# DTO Style

- Use Lombok for DTO boilerplate (`@Data`, constructors, and `@Builder` when useful).
- Keep DTOs transport-focused and aligned with API payload fields.
- Prefer primitive wrappers (`Long`, `Double`, `Integer`) for nullable API values.
- Allow lightweight utility helpers on DTOs when they directly support request building (for example price scaling helpers).
- Keep auth/payment DTOs minimal and explicit, with no persistence annotations.
